          <p class="text-gray-700">Case study structure required: Client name & industry (credibility), challenge (problem you solved), strategy (your thinking), execution (work you did), results (quantified outcomes: metrics, revenue impact, awards won), before/after visuals (transformation proof), testimonial (social proof). 500-800 words per case study minimum. Surface-level case studies ("we rebranded Catalyst Coffee") = weak. Deep-dive case studies (process, methodology, results) = strong.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="border-[3px] border-fuchsia-200 p-6">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-3">Should brand agencies show pricing or hide it?</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 mb-3"><strong>Show pricing ranges transparently. Transparency increases qualified leads 4x, saves 15+ hours monthly on unqualified inquiries.</strong> Prism Brand Studio added project pricing: "Brand Strategy $25-50K, Full Rebrand $75-150K." Qualified inquiries increased 4x (clients self-qualify before reaching out). Time saved: 18 hours/month previously spent responding to "how much does branding cost?" inquiries from $5K-budget clients. Win rate increased from 27% to 53% (better client fit).</p>
          <p class="text-gray-700">Best practice: Pricing ranges, not exact numbers. "Brand Strategy: $25-50K" accounts for project scope. Include what's included at each tier ("Tier 1 $25K: Brand strategy, visual identity, brand guidelines"). Include timeline ("6-8 weeks"). Include payment terms ("50% deposit, 50% on delivery"). Transparency filters out budget mismatches early. Clients who can afford your pricing inquire confidently. Clients who can't skip politely (everyone's time saved).</p>
